"v.撕裂；猛拉 【英】 v. 撕裂(to split or tear apart)；猛拉(to remove from place by violence; wrest) 【考】 反义词：unite(使联 合); mend(修补); repair(修理) 【例】 She wept and rent her garments. v. 撕裂(用力撕扯成小片) 【记】r, end: 撕裂一个人, 他就end了. Rend后需要mend 【类】rend: tear = rush: hurry 撕裂是过分撕 = 匆忙的做是过分仓卒 【反】unite(v 联合; 团结); mend = repair(v 修理) 【记】音：韧带 韧带容易撕裂； 【相关】wring 扭 rend (v.)  Old English rendan, hrendan ""to tear, cut down,"" from West Germanic *randijan (cognates: Old Frisian renda ""to cut, break,"" Middle Low German rende ""anything broken,"" German Rinde ""bark, crust""), probably related to rind. Related: Rended; rent; rending."
